com.edugility.objexj.parser
Class PostfixTokenizer

java.lang.Object
  java.text.ParsePosition
      com.edugility.objexj.parser.PostfixTokenizer
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<Token>
public class PostfixTokenizer
extends ParsePosition
implements Iterator<Token>

A ParsePosition and an Iterator of Tokens that converts a PushbackReader of a textual objexj pattern into a series of Tokens in postfix order.

A PostfixTokenizer is the lexer component of the lex-then-parse series of events that go into compiling an objexj pattern.

setIndex

public void setIndex(int index)
Sets the position of this PostfixTokenizer within its associated PushbackReader.

This method does not actually advance the PushbackReader; it is simply used to update an internal variable that keeps track of where the PushbackReader is within its stream.
